long: Yogeshwar Dutt is an Indian freestyle wrestler. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, he won the bronze medal in the 60 kg category. He was awarded the Padma Shri by the Government of India in 2013. He won a gold medal at the 2014 Commonwealth Games.

name: Sébastien Pocognoli
long: Sébastien Pocognoli is a Belgian international footballer who plays as a left back for Royale Union Saint-Gilloise in the Belgian First Division B.

name: Bradley Cooper
long: Bradley Charles Cooper is an American actor and filmmaker. He has been nominated for various awards, including eight Academy Awards and a Tony Award, and has won two Grammy Awards and a BAFTA Award.

name: Mick Jones
long: Michael Geoffrey Jones is a British musician, singer and songwriter best known as the lead guitarist, co-lead vocalist, co-founder and songwriter for The Clash until 1983. In 1984, he formed Big Audio Dynamite with Don Letts.

name: Adolf Hitler
long: Adolf Hitler was an Austrian-born German politician who was the dictator of Germany from 1933 to 1945. He rose to power as the leader of the Nazi Party, becoming Chancellor in 1933 and then Führer in 1934.

name: Xzibit
long: Alvin Nathaniel Joiner, better known by his stage name Xzibit, is an American rapper, actor, songwriter, television host, and radio personality.

name: Wayne Brady
long: Wayne Alphonso Brady is an American actor, singer, comedian, game show host, and television personality. He is a regular on the American version of the improvisational comedy television series Whose Line Is It Anyway?

name: William Gay
long: William Gay is an American football coach and former cornerback, who is the current defensive backs coach for the Missouri State Bears.

name: Nadine Garner
long: Nadine Lynette Garner is an Australian actress, who started her career as a teen performer.

name: Gene Wilder
long:
Jerome Silberman, known professionally as Gene Wilder, was an American actor, filmmaker, singer-songwriter, comedian and author.
Wilder began his career on stage, and made his screen debut in an episode of the TV series The Play of the Week in 1961.

name: Barack Obama
long: Barack Hussein Obama II is an American politician and attorney who served as the 44th president of the United States from 2009 to 2017. A member of the Democratic Party, Obama was the first African-American president of the United States.

name: Joe Biden
long: Joseph Robinette Biden Jr. is an American politician serving as the 46th president of the United States. A member of the Democratic Party, he served as the 47th vice president from 2009 to 2017 under Barack Obama and represented Delaware in the United States Senate from 1973 to 2009.

name: Rita Lee
long: Rita Lee Jones is a Brazilian rock singer, composer and writer. She is a former member of the Brazilian band Os Mutantes and is a popular figure in Brazilian entertainment, where she is also known for being an animal rights activist and a vegan.

name: Michelle Obama
long: Michelle LaVaughn Obama is an American attorney and author who was the first lady of the United States from 2009 to 2017. She is married to the 44th president of the United States, Barack Obama, and was the first African-American first lady.

name: Nancy Pelosi
short: Speaker of the United States House of Representatives
long: Nancy Patricia Pelosi is an American politician serving as Speaker of the United States House of Representatives since 2019, and previously from 2007 to 2011. She has served as a U.S. representative from California since 1987. A member of the Democratic Party, Pelosi is the only woman in U.S. history to serve as speaker.

name: Jeff Foxworthy
long: Jeffrey Marshall Foxworthy is an American comedian, actor, writer, producer, television personality, radio personality and author.

name: Donald Trump
long: Donald John Trump is an American media personality, businessman, and politician who served as the 45th president of the United States from 2017 to 2021.

name: Kevin Hart: Zero F**ks Given
long: Kevin Hart: Zero F**ks Given is a 2020 American stand-up comedy special by comedian Kevin Hart. According to Hart the special, which was shot in his living room, is going to be "like no other" having "zero filter" and making "zero apologies."
